			<div class="post-10008 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-spain">

				<div class="entry">

					<h2><a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/2013/01/10/spain-jobless-rate-hits-new-record-high-of-26-6-presstv/">Spain jobless rate hits new record high of 26.6%&nbsp;[presstv]</a></h2>

					<div class="post-info">
						<p>
							<span class="time">January 10, 2013</span>
															<span class="author">by <a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/author/mktgeistmike/" title="Posts by mktgeistmike" rel="author">mktgeistmike</a></span>
																						<span class="post-comments"><a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/2013/01/10/spain-jobless-rate-hits-new-record-high-of-26-6-presstv/#respond" title="Comment on Spain jobless rate hits new record high of 26.6%&nbsp;[presstv]">Leave a comment</a></span>
																				</p>
					</div>

					<div id="divLead">New data shows Spain’s jobless rate hit a new record high of 26.6 percent for the month of November 2012, amounting to 6.157 million Spaniards.</div>
<p><img id="imgMain" alt="People stand in line outside of an unemployment office in Madrid, Spain. (File photo)" src="http://previous.presstv.ir/photo/20130109/hedstrom20130109100944227.jpg" width="650px" height="365px" /></p>
<p>The European Union’s statistics office, Eurostat, released the new data on Tuesday, which showed an increase of 0.4 percent from October’s reading of 26.2 percent.</p>
<p>The EU&#8217;s Employment Commissioner Laszlo Andor urged Spain’s government to find a political strategy to decrease the number of people without work</p>
<p>Andor said he is extremely worried about the unemployment rate for the country’s youth under 25, which was reported at 56.5 percent in November 2012, a 0.7 percent increase from 55.8 in October last year.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.presstv.ir/detail/2013/01/09/282606/spain-jobless-rate-hits-record-266/">Read more</a></p>
<div class="clear"></div>

				</div>

